│ THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs because LoopVectorize widens a load whose pointer operand depends on a predicated sdiv. In inactive lanes, the sdiv result is poison, yet it is used to   │
│ form addresses for an unmasked wide load, causing UB. I implemented a guard in LoopVectorizationCostModel::memoryInstructionCanBeWidened to reject widening when the pointer operand is  │
│ tainted by predicated instructions (detected via a small DFS over the pointer’s def-use chain). This forces the vectorizer to choose a safe alternative (masked/gather or                │
│ scalarization), preventing the use of poison addresses in unmasked vector loads.                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
