│ THOUGHT: I implemented two changes to prevent UB from predicated address computation:                                                                                                    │
│ 1) In memoryInstructionCanBeWidened, we now reject widening if the pointer operand depends on a predicated instruction, so LV won’t emit unmasked consecutive vector loads/stores when   │
│ their addresses could be poison in inactive lanes.                                                                                                                                       │
│ 2) In isScalarWithPredication, we force scalarization for GEPs whose operands depend on predicated instructions, ensuring address formation happens under the predicate and doesn’t      │
│ propagate poison to vector GEPs.                                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
